core_metadata_found.title: Nutritional Survey Data from Montenegro - The NutriMont Project Datasets
core_metadata_found.summary:
Introduction

The datasets were created as part of the "Nutrition Survey in Montenegro - NutriMont", a research project falling under the domain of nutritional epidemiology and public health. The NutriMont project is an extensive study focusing on dietary habits, nutritional knowledge, and health indicators across diverse demographic groups in Montenegro.

Context and methodology

Primary Objective: The primary purpose of datasets is to gain insights into the nutritional patterns and health outcomes of the Montenegrin population. It aims to analyze how local dietary habits align with national and international nutritional guidelines and their impact on public health.

Secondary Objectives: The datasets also serves to inform policymakers and public health officials for developing targeted nutritional interventions and educational programs. It is intended to contribute to the broader body of research in nutrition and public health, providing valuable data for future studies and comparisons.

Data Collection Methods:

Primary Surveys: The datasets include data from primary surveys conducted in various regions of Montenegro. These surveys comprised a General Questionnaire, double 24-hour recall/food forms, and a Food Propensity Questionnaire (FPQ), designed to collect comprehensive information on dietary habits, health status, and socioeconomic factors.

Secondary Data Sources: Additionally, the dataset integrates secondary data extracted from existing datasets (Nutrition Landscape Information System (NLiS), NLiS Country Profile: Montenegro and the EFSA Comprehensive European Food Consumption Database) particularly to supplement or validate the primary survey data.

Technical details

  • Datasets Structure: The collected data are organized into several datasets: 1_NutriMont_DemoSocioData, encompassing demographic and sociodemographic survey data in .csv format; 2_NutriMont_MacronutrientData, containing detailed macronutrient intake information in .csv format; 3_NutriMont_ConsumptionData, focusing on average food consumption by different food categories in .csv format; and Data Visuals, comprising data visualizations in .png formats. 
  • General Accessibility: No specific software is required to access the data.
creator: Milacic, Andrea

metadata.title: Nutritional Survey Data from Montenegro - The NutriMont Project Datasets
metadata.summary:
Introduction

The datasets were created as part of the "Nutrition Survey in Montenegro - NutriMont", a research project falling under the domain of nutritional epidemiology and public health. The NutriMont project is an extensive study focusing on dietary habits, nutritional knowledge, and health indicators across diverse demographic groups in Montenegro.

Context and methodology

Primary Objective: The primary purpose of datasets is to gain insights into the nutritional patterns and health outcomes of the Montenegrin population. It aims to analyze how local dietary habits align with national and international nutritional guidelines and their impact on public health.

Secondary Objectives: The datasets also serves to inform policymakers and public health officials for developing targeted nutritional interventions and educational programs. It is intended to contribute to the broader body of research in nutrition and public health, providing valuable data for future studies and comparisons.

Data Collection Methods:

Primary Surveys: The datasets include data from primary surveys conducted in various regions of Montenegro. These surveys comprised a General Questionnaire, double 24-hour recall/food forms, and a Food Propensity Questionnaire (FPQ), designed to collect comprehensive information on dietary habits, health status, and socioeconomic factors.

Secondary Data Sources: Additionally, the dataset integrates secondary data extracted from existing datasets (Nutrition Landscape Information System (NLiS), NLiS Country Profile: Montenegro and the EFSA Comprehensive European Food Consumption Database) particularly to supplement or validate the primary survey data.

Technical details

  • Datasets Structure: The collected data are organized into several datasets: 1_NutriMont_DemoSocioData, encompassing demographic and sociodemographic survey data in .csv format; 2_NutriMont_MacronutrientData, containing detailed macronutrient intake information in .csv format; 3_NutriMont_ConsumptionData, focusing on average food consumption by different food categories in .csv format; and Data Visuals, comprising data visualizations in .png formats. 
  • General Accessibility: No specific software is required to access the data.
creator: Milacic, Andrea
